1 Download Debian 12 ISO 

For 32 Bit https://cdimage.debian.org/cdimage/archive/12.0.0/i386/iso-cd/
For Armel https://cdimage.debian.org/cdimage/archive/12.0.0/armel/iso-dvd/
For MIPS https://cdimage.debian.org/cdimage/archive/12.0.0/mipsel/
For MIPS 64 Bit https://cdimage.debian.org/cdimage/archive/12.0.0/mips64el/

2 Flash Debian 12 I386
3 Setup Debian 12 I386
4 If tasksel select gnome and debian desktop environment deselect it just standard system utilities
5 Run su - then run apt install sudo then nano /etc/sudoers then add yourusername on User privilege specification
6 Exit root then run sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y
7 Run sudo nano /etc/os-release
  Then Change Debian GNU/Linux 12 (bookworm) To Syslack Linux 1.3 (sunix)
  Then change Name Debian GNU/Linux To Syslack Linux
  Then change VERSION_ID 12 to 1.3
  Then change VERSION 12 (bookworm) to 1.3 (sunix)
  Then change VERSION_CODENAME bookworm to sunix
  Change ID=debian to ID=syslack
  Change the HOME_URL To https://github.com/syslacklinux/Syslack-Linux
  Change the SUPPORT_URL To https://github.com/syslacklinux/Syslack-Linux/discussions/3
  Change The BUG_REPORT_URL To https://github.com/syslacklinux/Syslack-Linux/issues/1
CTRL X Y ENTER
8 Run sudo nano /etc/issue Then change Debian GNU/Linux 12 \n \l To Syslack Linux 1.3 \n \l
9 Run sudo nano /etc/issue.net Then change Debian GNU/Linux 12 To Syslack Linux 1.3
10 Then sudo apt-mark hold base-files
11 Run sudo apt install links then links https://github.com/syslacklinux/Syslack-Linux Then save the Screenshot From 2026-01-31 16-31-30 Then name it to syslack-logo.png
12 Then sudo mv /home/yourusername/syslack-logo.png /usr/share/pixmaps then sudo cp /usr/share/pixmaps/syslack-logo.png /usr/share/pixmaps/debian-logo.png
13 Run sudo nano /etc/os-release then add LOGO=/usr/share/pixmaps/syslack-logo.png
14 Run sudo nano /etc/default/grub Then Remove Quiet On GRUB_CMDLINE_LINUX_DEFAULT Then On GRUB_DISTRIBUTOR Change To GRUB_DISTRIBUTOR="Syslack"
   Then sudo update-grub
15 Run sudo rm /etc/motd
16 Run sudo apt-mark hold desktop-base
17 Run sudo apt remove systemd then sudo apt --fix-broken install sudo apt install openrc
